reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Hardly works… no privacy and breaks SUPER easy
reviews.reviewText: The only reason I gave it more than 1 star is because it is a very well designed kit. Super easy to install and can’t even tell it’s there. That being said…. The “privacy” part is nearly useless. The phones brightness needs to be down 50% or more for the person next to you to actually not be able to see the screen. Sure, it dims the screen a bit. But at full brightness everything on screen is still completely visible and even text messages are entirely legible. That was my whole purpose of buying this, so someone sitting next to me couldn’t see my screen.As far as a protector goes, good quality. As far as a privacy protector goes, do NOT recommend.UPDATE: less than one week in, the first screen protector has cracked in several places. Look at the picture, you can see how bad it is. To put this in perspective, I’ve had an iPhone since the 4g came out well over a decade ago. I’ve never broken an iPhone screen except on my 4g (fell 40 feet from the top of bleachers. Nothing would save that lol). I’ve also never used screen protectors before. So well over a decade with zero broken screens with zero screen protection, yet this screen protector cracked in several places with less than one week of use? 100% not worth it. Do not waste your money on a “privacy” screen protector that doesn’t actually protect your privacy, and will crack with the slightest little bump. What’s the point of a screen protector that’s weaker than the screen it’s protecting? Or what’s the point of a “privacy” screen protector that allows far more visibility than it lets on in the ad? Theres a reason this thing is super cheap and comes with 4 in the pack. You’re gonna break it and need another in short order, and it’s not going to do what it says it does.DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON THIS.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good but questionable privacy screen
reviews.reviewText: I haven't dropped the phone to attest to its capabilities in protecting the screen. I do, however, notice that the privacy screen isn't private enough for me. I don't have anything to hide but I like to get what I pay for. The screen is still visible at a 45 degree angle. I had to lower the brightness of the screen to get the effect I was after. In doing so, the screen is....well darker and harder to see when looking straight at it which is not optimal. Anywho, I'm going to eventually drop the phone, so I'll be back with a review after that happens....maybe...

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 100% THE BEST screen protector! BUY IT!
reviews.reviewText: This screen protector saved my phone on the second day I had it installed. On vacation, it slipped out of my grip and fell hard face down onto an aggregate driveway. The screen protector sustained four chips along the edge and then cracked inward. I didn’t have a replacement with me but it held up great over the next three days. Once home I removed the damaged screen protector and saw that the phone sustained no damage! Installed a new protector this morning and I’m good to go.I would 100% highly recommend this kit! The alignment frames make installing the glass easy and foolproof.The protectors are glare free and smooth as silk, especially when using the slide keyboard.As far as value, this is the way to go. Four protectors with lens wipes, drying cloths, lint stickers and the alignment frames, which are reusable if needed make this the only way to go for protecting an expensive phone.Buy this kit!
